          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Disaster Recovery and Opportunity Act of 201</b><b>9</b></p> <p>This bill allows the chief executive officer (e.g., governor) of a state to designate certain population census tracts in areas related to federally declared disasters as opportunity zones. This makes investments in the areas eligible for various tax incentives. </p>]]></text>
